Even as the country prepares to mark three years since the political truce between President Kenyatta and ODM leader Raila Odinga, is the country slowly drifting back to political tensions and intolerance, 17 months to the next general election? This is the question on the minds of many following assertions by Odinga's political allies that the country risks going back to where it was if unnamed government operatives from Harambee house do not stop meddling in the handshake. KTN senior political reporter Chris Thairu dissects some of the likely political scenarios if Odinga decides to bolt out of the pact and some of the historic political agreements he has been forced to ditch.